WEBVTT

00:01.200 --> 00:21.960
18. And after these things I saw another angel come down from heaven, having great power,

00:22.240 --> 00:27.760
and the earth was lightened with his glory, and he cried mightily with a strong voice,

00:29.000 --> 00:35.700
Babylon the Great is fallen, is fallen, and is become the habitation of devils, and the

00:35.700 --> 00:41.960
hold of every foul spirit, and a cage of every unclean and hateful bird. For all nations

00:41.960 --> 00:46.420
have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her fornication, and the kings of the earth have

00:46.420 --> 00:51.540
committed fornication with her, and the merchants of the earth are waxed rich through the abundance

00:51.540 --> 00:59.100
of her delicacies. And I heard another voice from heaven saying, Come out of her, my people,

00:59.280 --> 01:05.460
that ye be not partakers of her sins, and that ye receive not of her plagues. For her sins have

01:05.460 --> 01:12.120
reached unto heaven, and God hath remembered her iniquities. Reward her even as she rewarded you,

01:12.320 --> 01:18.320
and double unto her double according to her works. In the cup which she hath filled, fill to her

01:18.320 --> 01:25.420
double. How much she hath glorified herself, and lived deliciously. So much torment and sorrow give

01:25.420 --> 01:32.760
her, for she saith in her heart, I sit a queen, and am no widow, and shall see no sorrow. Therefore

01:32.760 --> 01:38.860
shall her plagues come in one day, death and mourning and famine, and she shall be utterly

01:38.860 --> 01:45.660
burned with fire. For strong is the Lord God who judgeth her. And the kings of the earth who have

01:45.660 --> 01:51.740
committed fornication, and lived deliciously with her, shall bewail her, and lament for her, when they

01:51.740 --> 01:58.300
shall see the smoke of her burning, standing afar off for the fear of her torment, saying, Alas,

01:59.500 --> 02:07.980
alas, that great city Babylon, that mighty city, for in one hour is thy judgment come. And the

02:07.980 --> 02:14.440
merchants of the earth shall weep and mourn over her, for no man buyeth their merchandise any more.

02:14.440 --> 02:21.520
The merchandise of gold, and silver, and precious stones, and of pearls, and fine linen, and purple,

02:21.680 --> 02:28.500
and silk, and scarlet, and all fine wood, and all manner vessels of ivory, and all manner vessels of

02:28.500 --> 02:35.160
most precious wood, and of brass, and iron, and marble, and cinnamon, and odors, and ointments,

02:35.420 --> 02:42.300
and frankincense, and wine, and oil, and fine flour, and wheat, and beasts, and sheep, and horses,

02:42.300 --> 02:49.540
and chariots, and slaves, and souls of men. And the fruits that thy soul lusted after are departed

02:49.540 --> 02:55.540
from thee, and all things which were dainty and goodly are departed from thee, and thou shalt find

02:55.540 --> 03:02.480
them no more at all. The merchants of these things which were made rich by her shall stand afar off

03:02.480 --> 03:11.040
for the fear of her torment, weeping and wailing, and saying, Alas, alas, that great city that was

03:11.040 --> 03:18.200
clothed in fine linen, and purple, and scarlet, and decked with gold, and precious stones, and pearls,

03:18.520 --> 03:26.280
for in one hour so great riches is come to naught. And every shipmaster, and all the company in ships,

03:26.660 --> 03:32.860
and sailors, and as many as trade by sea, stood afar off, and cried when they saw the smoke of

03:32.860 --> 03:40.800
her burning, saying, What city is like unto this great city? And they cast dust on their heads,

03:40.800 --> 03:50.360
and cried, weeping and wailing, saying, Alas, alas, that great city wherein were made rich all that

03:50.360 --> 03:58.540
had ships in the sea by reason of her costliness, for in one hour is she made desolate. Rejoice over

03:58.540 --> 04:04.420
her, thou heaven, and ye holy apostles and prophets, for God hath avenged you on her.

04:05.220 --> 04:11.700
And a mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone, and cast it into the sea, saying,

04:12.420 --> 04:19.660
Thus with violence shall that great city Babylon be thrown down, and shall be found no more at all,

04:19.940 --> 04:26.080
and the voice of harpers, and musicians, and of pipers, and trumpeters shall be heard no more

04:26.080 --> 04:32.680
at all in thee, and no craftsman of whatsoever craft he be shall be found any more in thee,

04:32.680 --> 04:38.660
and the sound of a millstone shall be heard no more at all in thee, and the light of a candle

04:38.660 --> 04:44.440
shall shine no more at all in thee, and the voice of the bridegroom, and of the bride shall be heard

04:44.440 --> 04:50.840
no more at all in thee, for thy merchants were the great men of the earth, for by thy sorceries were

04:50.840 --> 04:57.720
all nations deceived, and in her was found the blood of prophets, and of saints, and of all that

04:57.720 --> 04:59.540
slain upon the earth.

05:01.040 --> 05:03.220
The end of chapter 18.

